en: Ooh...Ugh, what happened?
Error, Error, system overload. Proceeding to Reboot…... Reboot Complete!
Designated Ranger, the ships gravity engine malfunctioned. While I run diagnostics, make sure you can move efficiently. We have lots to do!
DIAGNOSTICS COMPLETE. I have bad news Ranger. The ship is totally wrecked, and the radar is…
Broken? No problem, I can fix that!
Don’t interrupt me! It’s not broken, it’s completely missing. Sir, this is not good.
Missing? Unless it fell out of the ship during the crash, it must have been stolen...Check the CCTV footage, quickly.
I tried doing that during my diagnostics, but I couldn’t access it. It seems like somebody is messing with my system in the main bay. Let me open the door and you go check it out.
ROGER, what is that thing over there?
HEY! I am not a thing; I am a Daran!
Well whatever you are, you must be the one messing with my ship!
Uh Oh...
HEY! COME BACK HERE!
What's radar?
A radar detects surrounding objects using radio waves.
A radar detects recently made cherry pie
A radar gets your favorite television shows
A radar detects surrounding objects using magic
What does RADAR stand for?
Raspberry Danish and Ravioli
Radio Detection and Ranging.
Rectangle Diamond and Rombas
Radio Destroyer and Reviver
How does a radar detect things?
Asks politely
Studies very hard

keys:
The radar transmits a pulse wave – usually shortwave 
 microwaves – at a certain time.
en:
The radar transmits a pulse wave – usually shortwave 
 microwaves – at a certain time.
Uses the MBSE model
What does the pulse wave do?
Finishes your math homework
The pulse travels through Jello and bounces off a spoon
Makes you act on impulse

keys:
The pulse travels through a medium (air, vacuum of space) 
 and bounces off an object.
en:
The pulse travels through a medium (air, vacuum of space) 
 and bounces off an object.
Why does it bounce off an object?
Once it bounces off the object, it comes back towards the radar.
It wants to be a gymnast
It wants to see how high it can jump
It’s coated in bouncy juice
How does the radar know where the object is?
It looks at it with binoculars

keys:
It finds the range by measuring the time the pulse was sent & 
 when the pulse returns & 
 divides it by 2
en:
It finds the range by measuring the time the pulse was sent & 
 when the pulse returns & 
 divides it by 2
It tries it’s best
It communicates with other radars within a 300-mile radius
What if the object is moving?
It puts pedal to the metal
It says, “SLOW DOWN!”

keys:
We can determine the direction & speed the object is moving by 
 looking at various positions over time
en:
We can determine the direction & speed the object is moving by 
 looking at various positions over time
It does not detect the object
That sounds awesome, what does a Radar look like?
What are you talking about, don’t you not have my radar? What were you doing on my ship?
I heard an explosion and wanted to see what was going on. When I got here, I saw your friends running off, so I assumed everyone was gone.
Friends? Unless ROGER grew some legs and ran off, no one else was on the ship but us two.
What about the Scein? And the Trolum? Or the Yappo? The Tendra? And the...what were they called? Oh yeah, the Lagna!
Sheiza, the aliens of this planet must have gotten on board while ROGER and I were out cold...
Ranger, while you were playing catch up with your new friend, I got access to the CCTV footage. You should come take a look at this; I will be waiting in the Comms room.
According to the video, it looks like there were 5 different aliens that took parts of the Radar.
Ok ROGER, is there any way you can track them down?
Sadly I cannot. Due to my reboot, most of my functionality was wiped clean.
Dango! First my ship crashes, then my radar is stolen, and now ROGER? How am I going to get this done?
Perhaps I can help!
Oh yeah? Why would you help us! I don’t even know your name...
The name is Daria! I am a Daran, the native species of Hertzich! I had so much fun with you earlier, I thought I would see if you wanted to play more!
And why should I trust you?
Do you have any other options?
Dango, you gotta point there...Alright, and how exactly can you help?
I’ve lived here all my life and I know this planet like the back of my paw. The big city, Yaplisdapolis, would have somewhere to fix your ship. I can show you how to get there!
The city? I saw that earlier when we were falling into the atmosphere, I don’t think it’s too far...but what about the missing radar? I would be flying blind in deep space without it!

Well, all the nice people I saw earlier had pieces of something, I bet that was your missing radar! I know a path that would lead into each major village of the other species on the planet, with the biiiiiig city at the end!
Well, it seems we really could use your help then...Ok hotshot, where to first?
The closest village would be in the Plains of Trolonc. That’s where the Trolums live. I bet we can find a part of your radar there!
Sounds good! ROGER, will you be ok on the ship?
Don’t worry Ranger, I have a piece of me in your suit, it will be like I never left your side. Gotta make sure you stay on track.
This will be so much fun!
